sourcesContent: import React, { useState } from "react" const Register = () => { const [value, setValue] = useState({ name: "", email: "", age: "", mobile: "", work: "", add: "", desc: "", }) const setdata = (e) => { const { name, value } = e.target setValue((preval) => { return { ...preval, [name]: value, } }) } const handleSubmit = async (e) => { e.prevent.default() const { name, email, age, mobile, work, add, desc } = value const res = await fetch("https://loacalhost:8003/register", { method: "POST", headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json", }, body: JSON.stringify({ name, email, age, mobile, work, add, desc, }), }) const data = await res.json() console.log(data) if (res.status === 422 || !data) { alert("error") console.log("error") } else { alert("data added") console.log("data added") } } return (
